</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="55.[151,1436,1701,2007]" lastBlockId="56.[151,1436,152,578]" lastPageId="56" lastPageNumber="57" pageId="55" pageNumber="56">
<emphasis box="[198,772,1941,1966]" italics="true" pageId="55" pageNumber="56">
Description of male from Shelta Cave, 
<collectingRegion box="[657,766,1941,1966]" country="United States of America" name="Alabama" pageId="55" pageNumber="56">Alabama</collectingRegion>
:
</emphasis>
Length, 
<quantity box="[885,978,1941,1967]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="7.5" pageId="55" pageNumber="56" unit="mm" value="7.5">7.5 mm</quantity>
, width, 
<quantity box="[1072,1165,1941,1967]" metricMagnitude="-4" metricUnit="m" metricValue="7.0" pageId="55" pageNumber="56" unit="mm" value="0.7">0.7 mm</quantity>
. Nonsexual characters as described for genus. Gonopods (
<figureCitation box="[582,671,1981,2007]" captionStart="FIGURES 83–86" captionStartId="56.[151,269,1966,1990]" captionTargetBox="[183,1413,644,1916]" captionTargetId="figure-192@56.[168,1419,634,1942]" captionTargetPageId="56" captionText="FIGURES 83–86. Scoterpes spp. males, anterior view of gonopods. 83. S. alabama. 84. S. jackdanieli. 85. S. willreevesi. 86. S. syntheticus." pageId="55" pageNumber="56">Fig. 83</figureCitation>
) with completely fused coxosternum; angiocoxal setal groups well-separated, distal group of 3 setae. Mesal angiocoxal branch longer or equal to lateral, flat, bladelike, slightly twisted, acuminate. Lateral branch more cylindrical, slightly decurved or knobbed apically. Fimbriate branch prominent, thin, lamellate, seemingly made of fused linear fibers, marginally and apically serrate. Ninth legs typical of genus.
</paragraph>
